  "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
  "body": "#### Overview of the Issue\r\n\r\nCurrently, vitess returns an error if the trace information sent along with the query cannot be decoded successfully. This feels like wrong behavior and I believe Vitess should skip tracing the request and just execute the SQL query without emitting the traces.\r\n\r\n#### Reproduction Steps\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce this issue, example:\r\n\r\n1. Enable the opentracing jaeger flag on a vtgate ```-tracer opentracing-jaeger```\r\n2. Login to a mysql shell on the vtgate ```mysql --comments```\r\n3. Send a query with invalid trace information. In this case, i sent a trace id that is longer than 32 characters which jaeger does not support.\r\n```\r\nmysql> /*VT_SPAN_CONTEXT=eyJ1YmVyLXRyYWNlLWlkIjoiODI4MjExRDctNjQzQi00OEQyLUE3NzktMUIwMDAzMDM1MjQyOjhlOWU4YzgxZmRlNTlkMDc6YzM3YTkzZjdkNWI1MWQ5ODoxIn0=*/select hi from hello limit 10\\G\r\nERROR 1105 (HY000): unknown error: TraceID cannot be longer than 32 hex characters: 822211D7-613B-98D2-A759-1B0003035242\r\nfailed to deserialize span context\r\nfailed to extract span\r\n```\r\n4. Notice Vitess returns an error\r\n\r\n#### Binary version\r\nWe are running the 7.0 build",
